Introduction

Hanni Phạm is a Vietnamese-Australian singer-songwriter, dancer, and composer under ADOR and HYBE Labels. She is best known as a member of the girl group NewJeans.

Born and raised in Melbourne, Australia, Hanni is the eldest daughter of Vietnamese parents. At a young age, she showed great passion for music, leading to her auditioning for 'The Voice Kid Australia' and joining a Kpop dance cover group with her friends. Soon after, she participated in the 'Plus Global Audtion' and became a trainee under Source Music. Eventually, she joined the label ADOR, making way to her debut as a member of NewJeans.

On July, 22, 2022, Hanni officially debuted as a member of NewJeans with their self-titled mini debut album "NewJeans".
